So far it all seems pretty straight forward, but usually we would like to see accuracy among many different Probability Thresholds. For our example we will use the Carseats data set from the ISLR package that provides a collection of data sets to the highly recommended ISLR book.
For this tutorial I will use the code from ISLR tidymodels Labs (which is also highly recommended). We will try to predict high sales by dichotomising the Sales variable, and split the data to train and test set with the help of the rsample package:



